HEADWORD: Pericardial
<hw>Per`i*car"di*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or
pertaining to pericardium; situated around the heart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pericardial fluid</b></col> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>, <cd>a
serous fluid of a pale yellow color contained in the
pericardium.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

